 <fr:p>Fixing <fr:tex>S\subseteq  A</fr:tex>, we compute:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block">   \begin {aligned}     {\mathopen {}\left  [\chi _{S}\right  ]\mathclose {}} &amp;= {\mathopen {}\left \{a\in  A\,\middle \vert \,\chi _S{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=1\right \}\mathclose {}}\\     &amp;= {\mathopen {}\left \{a\in  A\,\middle \vert \,a\in  S\right \}\mathclose {}}\\     &amp;= S   \end {aligned}  </fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Conversely, we fix <fr:tex>\phi \colon  A \to  {\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}</fr:tex> and compute:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block">   \begin {aligned}   \chi _{{\mathopen {}\left  [\phi \right  ]\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} &amp;= \begin {cases}    1 &amp; \text {if } a \in  {\mathopen {}\left  [\phi \right  ]\mathclose {}}\\    0 &amp; \text {if } a \not \in {\mathopen {}\left  [\phi \right  ]\mathclose {}}   \end {cases}   \\   &amp;=   \begin {cases}    1 &amp;\text {if } \phi {\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=1\\    0 &amp;\text {if } \phi {\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\not =1   \end {cases}   \\   &amp;=   \begin {cases}    1 &amp;\text {if } \phi {\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=1\\    0 &amp;\text {if } \phi {\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=0   \end {cases}   \\   &amp;= \phi {\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}   \end {aligned}  </fr:tex>
